sources.title: Night Cargo
sources.description: A talky low-budget melodrama supposedly set in the far east. So if you're wondering why Julie Bishop plays a Latin-American dancer in a Singapore cafe, so am I. Glitchy print. Directed by Charles Hutchison. Released in 1936. 12 minutes are missing.

metadata.Plot: While in Singapore, a man and a pretty young girl find themselves mixed up in blackmail and murder.
metadata.Actors: Lloyd Hughes, Julie Bishop, Walter Miller
